  "prompt": "Can I make a voice call from my iPad using Jio SIM?",
  "response": "Yes, you can make a voice call from your iPad using a Jio SIM, provided that your iPad supports cellular connectivity and has a SIM card slot. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Check iPad Compatibility**: Ensure that your iPad model supports cellular connectivity and has a SIM card slot (either physical or eSIM). If your iPad is Wi-Fi only, you won\u2019t be able to use a Jio SIM for calls.\n\n2. **Insert Jio SIM**: Insert the Jio SIM into the iPad's SIM card slot or activate the Jio eSIM if your iPad supports eSIM.\n\n3. **Enable Cellular Data**: Go to **Settings > Cellular Data** and ensure that cellular data is enabled for Jio.\n\n4. **Make a Voice Call**:\n   - If your iPad supports **Voice over LTE (VoLTE)**, you can make voice calls directly using the Phone app or FaceTime app (if configured with your Jio number).\n   - Alternatively, you can use the **JioChat** or **JioCall** app (downloadable from the App Store) to make voice calls over the internet using your Jio number.\n\n5. **Use FaceTime Audio (Optional)**: If you don't need to use your Jio number specifically, you can make audio calls using FaceTime Audio to other Apple devices linked with the caller's Apple ID.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Not all iPad models support voice calls directly through the Phone app. For such models, you\u2019ll need to use apps like JioChat or JioCall.\n- Ensure that your Jio SIM is activated and has an active plan supporting voice calls.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, contact Jio customer support for assistance.",
